\subsubsection{a}
It depends from the point of view. It appears to be low, because the range of the eigenvalues is short.
\subsubsection{b}
Yes, since the range is short also the approximation error will be low.
\subsubsection{c}
The median of the dimensions should be fine. The $50$ dimension, where $\lambda_50 = 1$. 

